2 unit Ciabatta Roll
2 ounce Mixed Greens
4 ounce Fresh Mozzarella
2 unit Roma Tomato
5 teaspoon Balsamic Vinegar
½ ounce Almonds
2 tablespoon Crème Fraîche
1 clove Garlic
Salt
Pepper
½ ounce Basil
2 teaspoon Olive Oil

Wash and dry all produce.

Pick basil leaves from stems; finely chop leaves. Peel and mince or grate garlic. Halve ciabattas; toast until golden if desired. Halve tomatoes lengthwise; slice crosswise into half-moons. Thinly slice mozzarella into rounds.

In a medium bowl, toss mixed greens and almonds with vinegar and a large drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.

In a small bowl, combine crème fraîche and chopped basil with garlic to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Spread creamy basil sauce onto cut sides of ciabattas. Fill with tomatoes, mozzarella, and a bit of salad.

Halve sandwiches on a diagonal and divide between plates. Toss any remaining tomatoes into remaining salad; serve on the side.